  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>
      活動
    </h1>
    <ol>
      <li>
        持續按重設模擬鍵直到出現至少兩個帶正電的粒子(紅色)與至少兩個帶負電的粒子(藍色)。
		此外，
		所有帶電粒子必須帶有不同的電量。
		從右側的拖動條中觀察各個粒子的帶電量，
		但不要做任何調整。
		你可以拖拉粒子以改變其位置，
		並試著分辨出哪個粒子是粒子1，
		哪個粒子是粒子2等等。
		等到五個粒子都分辨出來後，
		你可以利用拖動條改變粒子的帶電量來確認答案，
		改變粒子的正負將會有很大的幫助。
      </li>
    </ol>
  </body>
</html>

Content.Code:
for (int index=0; index<n; index++)
{
  x[index] = -10.0 + 20.0*Math.random();
  y[index] = -10.0 + 20.0*Math.random();
  q[index] = Math.round(-30.0 + 60.0*Math.random());
}
// Math.random() gives a random number between 0 and 1
// Multiplying Math.random() by 20 gives a random number between
// 0 and 20
// Subtracting 10 then gives a random number between -10 and 10
// In the "for" loop, the value of index starts at 0, and then
// increases by 1 at the end of each loop (index++ increments it).
// Keep looping as long as index is less than n
// The loop is the set of statements between the braces
// { at the beginning, and } at the end

q0 = q[0];
q1 = q[1];
q2 = q[2];
q3 = q[3];
q4 = q[4];

int i;   // declare an integer we will use as a loop index

// Calculating force components

// First, set the components of all the net forces to zero
for (i=0; i<n; i++)
{
  FxNet[i] = 0.0;
  FyNet[i] = 0.0;
}

// Now, we'll find the components of all the individual forces.
// The first loop runs from 0 to n-2
// The second loop just runs from i+1 to n-1
// Each calculation takes some time, so we're minimizing that
// time by doing as few calculations as we can
// We declare a new variable, dSq, here, too (distance squared)

for (i=0; i<(n-1); i++)
{
  for (int j=i+1; j<n; j++)
  {
    double dSq = (x[j]-x[i])*(x[j]-x[i]) + (y[j]-y[i])*(y[j]-y[i]);
    // The force particle i feels because of particle j
    Fx[i][j] = -(k*q[i]*q[j]/dSq)*(x[j]-x[i])/Math.sqrt(dSq);
    Fy[i][j] = -(k*q[i]*q[j]/dSq)*(y[j]-y[i])/Math.sqrt(dSq);
    FxNet[i] = FxNet[i] + Fx[i][j];      // add to i's net force
    FyNet[i] = FyNet[i] + Fy[i][j];
        // The force particle j feels because of particle i
    Fx[j][i] = -Fx[i][j];
    Fy[j][i] = -Fy[i][j];
    FxNet[j] = FxNet[j] + Fx[j][i];      // add to j's net force
    FyNet[j] = FyNet[j] + Fy[j][i];
  }   // end of the j loop
}  // end of the i loop

// This part sets the color of each particle
// depending on its charge
for (i=0; i<n; i++)
{
  if (q[i] > 0.0)
 {
  redness = 250;  // if it gets here the charge is positive
  greenness = 0;  // so we color the particle red
  blueness = 0;
  colorball[i] = new java.awt.Color(redness,greenness,blueness);
  }
  else
  {
    if (q[i] < 0.0)
    {
    redness = 0;    // if it gets here the charge is negative
    greenness = 0;  // so we color the particle blue
    blueness = 250;
    colorball[i] = new java.awt.Color(redness,greenness,blueness);
    }
    else
    {
    redness = 200;     // if it gets here the charge is zero
    greenness = 200;   // so we color the particle gray
    blueness = 200;
    colorball[i] = new java.awt.Color(redness,greenness,blueness);
    }  
  }
}

